HEADWORD: Supereminent
<hw>Su`per*em"i*nent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>supereminens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>supereminere</ets>. See
<er>Super-</er>, and <er>Eminent</er>.]</ety> <def>Eminent in a superior
degree; surpassing others in excellence; <as>as, a <ex>supereminent</ex>
divine; the <ex>supereminent</ex> glory of Christ</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Su`per*em"i*nent*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
